<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1082,1418]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,553,1198,1224]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
From 
<geoCoordinate box="[631,732,1198,1224]" degrees="1" direction="north" minutes="11" orientation="latitude" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" precision="925" value="1.1833334">1°11’N–</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[732,826,1198,1224]" degrees="11" direction="south" minutes="10" orientation="latitude" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" precision="925" value="-11.166667">11°10’S</geoCoordinate>
and 56°00’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[989,1098,1198,1224]" degrees="77" direction="west" minutes="40" orientation="longitude" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" precision="925" value="-77.666664">77°40’W</geoCoordinate>
in the central and western Amazon region in 
<collectingCountry box="[378,500,1237,1263]" name="Colombia" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[513,590,1237,1263]" name="Brazil" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[603,662,1237,1263]" name="Peru" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[726,815,1237,1263]" name="Bolivia" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
at 193(122–400) m elevation in lowland rainforest (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,1276,1302]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="100.[151,257,1196,1219]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,160,1161]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[151,1436,145,1171]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 26. Distribution maps of Geonoma maxima subsp. compta, G. maxima subsp. dispersa, G. maxima subsp. hexasticha, and G. maxima subsp. multiramosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3538414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3538414/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1082,1418]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
Some specimens from the Colombian Amazon (e.g., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Galeano 1973, García-Barriga 15005, Zarucchi 1712</emphasis>
) have wider pinnae than the others, more like those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Spruce" box="[853,1059,1353,1379]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="maxima" subSpecies="hexasticha">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[934,1059,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">hexasticha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. One specimen from Amazonas in 
<collectingCountry box="[181,235,1392,1418]" name="Peru" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[252,373,1392,1418]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Díaz 7131</emphasis>
) appears intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Trail" box="[746,913,1392,1418]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="maxima" subSpecies="compta">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[827,913,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">compta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Burret" box="[970,1207,1392,1418]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="maxima" subSpecies="camptoneura">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1052,1207,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">camptoneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
